 "text_ar": "تَجْمَعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the sheave of a large pulley"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 667}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with what is on each side of the latter;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for it seems to mean here, also, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pivot"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (K:) some say that it is so called because it turns round, returning to the point from which it departed: others, that it is so called because, by its revolving, it is polished so that it becomes white: (Zj:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maHaAwiru", "text_ar": "مَحَاوِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (A.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaliqato maHaAwiruhu", "text_ar": "قَلِقَتْ مَحَاوِرُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His circumstances,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "affair,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "case,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became unsettled:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, K:) from the state of the pin of the sheave of a pulley when it becomes smooth, and the hole becomes large, so that it wabbles. (A.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A thing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of iron"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon which turns the tongue of a buckle at the end of a waist-belt."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An iron instrument for cauterizing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a circular form:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see 2]. (K.) ―         -b4-  And The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wooden implement"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the baker,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "maker of bread,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with which he expands the dough,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and prepares it, and makes it round, to put it into the hot ashes in which it is baked:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) so called because of its turning round upon the dough, as being likened to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mHwr", "text_ar": "محور"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the sheave of a pulley, and because of its roundness. (T.)"}], "source_refs": ["K", "Zj", "A", "TA", "S"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}